main event: Military personnel aboard the USS Franklin D. Roosevelt observed a round, glowing object traveling at high speed, crossing the bow of the ship and disappearing in about 12 seconds on September 30, 1952.
interesting points: The object was reported to be about 20 to 25 feet in diameter and was luminous in appearance.
It was traveling at a very high speed and no sound was detected.
Observations were made by experienced aviation personnel, lending credibility to the sighting.
Photographic materials related to the sighting at sea included three 4x5 photographic negatives and one 8x10 photographic negative or transparency.
The sighting was part of the NATO maneuvers, and additional sightings of cigar-shaped objects were reported over various areas in Southern Norway during the same time period.
sighted object: round, glowing object traveling at high speed
location: USS Franklin D. Roosevelt, latitude 42 degrees 30 minutes north, longitude 68 degrees 16 minutes west
photographs: photographic materials related to the sighting at sea were included in the report
